The most effective strategy for new IT-based start-ups that want to target the Islamic market as well as the Chinese market would be to first carry out extensive market research in order to get an understanding of the particular requirements and inclinations of each of these target demographics. This may involve research on the religious and cultural norms held by Muslim customers, as well as research into the preferences held by Chinese consumers about technical developments and trends. Additionally, in order for the start-up to develop credibility and reach in these areas, it would be essential for them to form partnerships with local firms and influential individuals. Localization of the language and conformity with the local norms and legislation are two aspects that should be taken into consideration. 